<img srcset="https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/ToTDja73tYHYYSCbYFB9ZwKNnB0=/0x0:1504x1000/320x0/filters:focal(0x0:1504x1000):no_upscale()/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_asset/file/19394346/gyllenhaal_zodiac.jpg 320w, https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/VuIcD-e_BOqpgHdNoNsd7aUi1ak=/0x0:1504x1000/520x0/filters:focal(0x0:1504x1000):no_upscale()/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_asset/file/19394346/gyllenhaal_zodiac.jpg 520w, https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/tJnDjS25_XsT98p1Ao411I8zdoA=/0x0:1504x1000/720x0/filters:focal(0x0:1504x1000):no_upscale()/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_asset/file/19394346/gyllenhaal_zodiac.jpg 720w, https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/vNznEVfvUrx4lxOmtNOx6295UDw=/0x0:1504x1000/920x0/filters:focal(0x0:1504x1000):no_upscale()/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_asset/file/19394346/gyllenhaal_zodiac.jpg 920w, https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/ATk6dZdOKmnL1pfsOdeFlXj4TPI=/0x0:1504x1000/1120x0/filters:focal(0x0:1504x1000):no_upscale()/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_asset/file/19394346/gyllenhaal_zodiac.jpg 1120w, https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/3mZAshDSqGbzQ7p9eIKhrR6wzec=/0x0:1504x1000/1320x0/filters:focal(0x0:1504x1000):no_upscale()/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_asset/file/19394346/gyllenhaal_zodiac.jpg 1320w, https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/zqOPuIX71yapBFso4ZXP3fo70dY=/0x0:1504x1000/1520x0/filters:focal(0x0:1504x1000):no_upscale()/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_asset/file/19394346/gyllenhaal_zodiac.jpg 1520w, https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/P-5CXUp1p3o7-bK79qjwpjuAyoM=/0x0:1504x1000/1720x0/filters:focal(0x0:1504x1000):no_upscale()/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_asset/file/19394346/gyllenhaal_zodiac.jpg 1720w, https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/_h3DTsFK9180Ih0QkuZEluOOBAY=/0x0:1504x1000/1920x0/filters:focal(0x0:1504x1000):no_upscale()/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_asset/file/19394346/gyllenhaal_zodiac.jpg 1920w" sizes="(min-width: 1221px) 846px, (min-width: 880px) calc(100vw - 334px), 100vw" alt="" data-upload-width="1504" src="https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/c2Y0YcHn_2rdzgz7HOKjHHvG12U=/0x0:1504x1000/1200x0/filters:focal(0x0:1504x1000):no_upscale()/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_asset/file/19394346/gyllenhaal_zodiac.jpg">

</source></picture>

      
    </span>
    
  </span>
  
    <span class="e-image__meta">
      
      
        <cite>Paramount Pictures</cite>
      
    </span>
  
</figure>

<p id="jObX5O">Another journalist named Paul Avery (Robert Downey Jr.) originally sets out to discover the identity of a serial killer who calls himself the Zodiac, but cartoonist Graysmith becomes completely obsessed with the case. </p>
<p id="Fgtx3i"><strong>Does the character get their story? </strong>The Zodiac Killer’s identity remains one of the most famous unsolved crimes in the United States, so Graysmith was not able to crack the case, although he did write a bestselling book called <em>Zodiac</em> about it.<strong> 6/10</strong></p>
<p id="gEuhKV"><strong>Are they competent? </strong>At investigating the Zodiac killer, Graysmith turns out to be incredibly competent. He does get fired from his job as the newspaper’s cartoonist, though, so:<strong> 5/10</strong></p>
<p id="m7HkUn"><strong>Are they ethical?</strong> Graysmith is frequently described as a Boy Scout for his by-the-book habits.<strong> 10/10 </strong></p>
<p id="1tenqx"><strong>How believable is the journalist? </strong>Gyllenhaal went so far as to videotape Graysmith <a href="https://web.archive.org/web/20070927225954/http://media.movieweb.com/galleries/3158/notes.pdf">to study his mannerisms</a>, and nails his journey from earnest cartoonist to paranoid investigator. <strong>10/10 </strong></p>
<p id="UxAe4a"><strong>Total: 31/40 </strong></p>
<h4 id="e1SQqh">11. Jesse Eisenberg as David Lipsky in <em>The End of the Tour </em>(2015) </h4>
<p id="vdXUV5">Based on a true story, Lipsky trails writer David Foster Wallace (Jason Segel) around for a profile just as Foster Wallace’s literary stardom has turned into celebrity. </p>
<p id="4pFTwl"><strong>Does the character get their story? </strong>Not at first—the profile for which Lipsky spent a week with Wallace to write was never published. But Lipsky eventually writes the definitive book on Wallace, relying on the transcripts of their conversations during that week, so <strong>7/10</strong>.</p>
<p id="A9b89Z"><strong>Are they competent? </strong>Even thought Lipsky is self-conscious about how his career stacks up to Wallace’s celebrity-writer status, he is shown to be a gainfully employed and well-respected magazine journalist, so his biggest issue is confidence, not competence. And he’s clearly a great interviewer. <strong>8/10</strong> </p>
<p id="WTy71r"><strong>Are they ethical?</strong> Yes, he is very ethical in general, although he falters by becoming far too friendly with Wallace and staying at his house. <strong>6.5/10 </strong></p>
<p id="sshy5j"><strong>How believable is the journalist? </strong>I’m not sure an actor has ever resembled a certain type of journalist more than Eisenberg, who stammers and hems and haws and looks like he’s perpetually on the verge of spilling ink all over himself. <strong>10/10 </strong></p>
<p id="a0BB2o"><strong>Total: 31.5/40 </strong></p>
<h4 id="NppceA">10a. Patrick Fugit as William Miller in<em> Almost Famous </em>(2000)</h4>
  <figure class="e-image">
  <span class="e-image__inner">
    
    <span class="e-image__image " data-original="https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_asset/file/19394347/fugit_almost_famous.jpg">
      
