  <source srcset="https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/KwoJjeI19He_mjaA3aaZffjXYd0=/0x0:1020x576/320x0/filters:focal(0x0:1020x576):format(webp):no_upscale()/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_asset/file/19394347/fugit_almost_famous.jpg 320w, https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/BwnSAA6CcVO4blnzIe5zXU0KSU8=/0x0:1020x576/520x0/filters:focal(0x0:1020x576):format(webp):no_upscale()/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_asset/file/19394347/fugit_almost_famous.jpg 520w, https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/za4f4rV27xtLj9XeI9e3dAwOnTo=/0x0:1020x576/720x0/filters:focal(0x0:1020x576):format(webp):no_upscale()/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_asset/file/19394347/fugit_almost_famous.jpg 720w, https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/cGgSRi9JdvhQDAajSFMIcgDLjYM=/0x0:1020x576/920x0/filters:focal(0x0:1020x576):format(webp):no_upscale()/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_asset/file/19394347/fugit_almost_famous.jpg 920w, https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/rmfJgqTfzdyKYq-OrwfUurPYdwk=/0x0:1020x576/1120x0/filters:focal(0x0:1020x576):format(webp):no_upscale()/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_asset/file/19394347/fugit_almost_famous.jpg 1120w, https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/YXcmAYTv13CiSNLxCVpgbL8PhQE=/0x0:1020x576/1320x0/filters:focal(0x0:1020x576):format(webp):no_upscale()/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_asset/file/19394347/fugit_almost_famous.jpg 1320w, https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/CQgAGRIRrWlJftSStAEBF61gyuA=/0x0:1020x576/1520x0/filters:focal(0x0:1020x576):format(webp):no_upscale()/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_asset/file/19394347/fugit_almost_famous.jpg 1520w, https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/luRETF_0m5ix35JPQh0Ntw7yhqM=/0x0:1020x576/1720x0/filters:focal(0x0:1020x576):format(webp):no_upscale()/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_asset/file/19394347/fugit_almost_famous.jpg 1720w, https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/FwWPAg_w-BsPGPeECllUru-to6w=/0x0:1020x576/1920x0/filters:focal(0x0:1020x576):format(webp):no_upscale()/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_asset/file/19394347/fugit_almost_famous.jpg 1920w" sizes="(min-width: 1221px) 846px, (min-width: 880px) calc(100vw - 334px), 100vw" type="image/webp">


<img srcset="https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/pV-hbf2z77NTz5sx-uMvsYPz6X0=/0x0:1020x576/320x0/filters:focal(0x0:1020x576):no_upscale()/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_asset/file/19394347/fugit_almost_famous.jpg 320w, https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/So5bZSzGMsKV3Itzc3APGvlpU-w=/0x0:1020x576/520x0/filters:focal(0x0:1020x576):no_upscale()/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_asset/file/19394347/fugit_almost_famous.jpg 520w, https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/_yQ6gxbsqoAN1PX0Q-sMAFY5I64=/0x0:1020x576/720x0/filters:focal(0x0:1020x576):no_upscale()/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_asset/file/19394347/fugit_almost_famous.jpg 720w, https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/_26H3GXClIlv2ds0yyTmP86mTGU=/0x0:1020x576/920x0/filters:focal(0x0:1020x576):no_upscale()/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_asset/file/19394347/fugit_almost_famous.jpg 920w, https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/zb5LrMj6WbRUiDgTXOkKvqbf4pU=/0x0:1020x576/1120x0/filters:focal(0x0:1020x576):no_upscale()/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_asset/file/19394347/fugit_almost_famous.jpg 1120w, https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/8tXX4WCJOctRhZvMnrfRXBT6cwo=/0x0:1020x576/1320x0/filters:focal(0x0:1020x576):no_upscale()/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_asset/file/19394347/fugit_almost_famous.jpg 1320w, https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/vLJ9M81wFVXwU1yVv0XK-uN3GvU=/0x0:1020x576/1520x0/filters:focal(0x0:1020x576):no_upscale()/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_asset/file/19394347/fugit_almost_famous.jpg 1520w, https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/y-MezU23wo1dP0m66YAN6v550b8=/0x0:1020x576/1720x0/filters:focal(0x0:1020x576):no_upscale()/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_asset/file/19394347/fugit_almost_famous.jpg 1720w, https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/OVwj6U-M-7AF9y-j0YScYSh5UsE=/0x0:1020x576/1920x0/filters:focal(0x0:1020x576):no_upscale()/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_asset/file/19394347/fugit_almost_famous.jpg 1920w" sizes="(min-width: 1221px) 846px, (min-width: 880px) calc(100vw - 334px), 100vw" alt="" data-upload-width="1020" src="https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/KPUW5gR4F0mGmWOVXVfb_wWDgC8=/0x0:1020x576/1200x0/filters:focal(0x0:1020x576):no_upscale()/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_asset/file/19394347/fugit_almost_famous.jpg">

</source></picture>

      
    </span>
    
  </span>
  
    <span class="e-image__meta">
      
      
        <cite>DreamWorks</cite>
      
    </span>
  
</figure>

<p id="yYnZVF">Aspiring journalist and teenager Miller trails the rock band Stillwater in this semiautobiographical Cameron Crowe movie. </p>
<p id="2djnJu"><strong>Does the character get their story? </strong>Yes, he does ultimately get the story, although it is initially rejected because band leader Russell lies to the <em>Rolling Stone </em>fact checker and says William falsified his first draft. William needs his mom’s help to convince Russell to participate and verify the story. Points for writing a great story; slight deduction for the mom thing. <strong>8/10 </strong></p>
<p id="IaygXx"><strong>Are they competent? </strong>Yes, he’s a journalistic prodigy, good enough to gain the attention of a national magazine while he’s still a teenager. He does, however, falter at meeting deadlines and delivering his first cover story on time, so<strong> 8/10</strong></p>
<p id="juebK5"><strong>Are they ethical?</strong> “You cannot make friends with the rock stars,” Lester Bangs (Philip Seymour Hoffman) counsels Miller. Miller doesn’t listen. But apart from the friendliness, he’s pretty ethical, so <strong>6/10</strong></p>
<p id="IlUiFA"><strong>How believable is the journalist? </strong>This is Crowe’s most plainly autobiographical film, as he was a teenage journalism prodigy who profiled bands for <em>Rolling Stone</em> in the ’70s, and William Miller is deliberately modeled after him. <strong>10/10</strong></p>
<p id="A37N6E"><strong>Total: 32/40 </strong></p>
<h4 id="5Ulk4s">10b. Michael Nyqvist as Mikael Blomkvist in <em>The Girl With the Dragon Tattoo </em>(2009) </h4>
<p id="VmMcVl">Blomkvist starts this series as a disgraced indie magazine publisher and redeems himself through hacker-assisted journalism. </p>
<p id="LF6GSy"><strong>Does the character get their story? </strong>Yes, and he is able to basically completely rejuvenate a career maligned by scandal by writing a story from prison.<strong> 10/10 </strong></p>
<p id="4rLLFi"><strong>Are they competent? </strong>Blomkvist is a good investigator, but he does rely a lot on his research assistant, Lisbeth Salander (Noomi Rapace), who’s the one doing a large amount of the legwork. We’ll give Blomkvist a <strong>7/10</strong> </p>
<p id="6oApVI"><strong>Are they ethical?</strong> Yes, mostly—he doesn’t deserve to lose the libel case that causes him to go to prison—but he shouldn’t be sleeping with his freakin’ research assistant. <strong>7/10</strong></p>
<p id="ASXQrp"><strong>How believable is the journalist? </strong>He looks exactly how I’d imagine an ornery independent financial magazine owner in Scandinavia to look. The least-believable thing is that he’d ever take on a partner. <strong>8/10</strong></p>
<p id="DXFpyO"><strong>Total: 32/40 </strong></p>
<h4 id="hTVjtE">9. Cary Grant as Walter Burns and Rosalind Russell as Hildy Johnson in <em>His Girl Friday</em>
</h4>
<p id="0NC54h">Recently divorced<em> Morning Post </em>reporters and editors Hildy (Russell) and Walter (Grant) tackle one last crime scoop together. </p>
<p id="cKThjT"><strong>Does the character get their story? </strong>Yes, they manage to uncover the truth and help set an innocent man free. (Although Hildy doesn’t actually file the story before the movie ends.)<strong> 10/10 </strong></p>
<p id="koMBy2"><strong>Are they competent? </strong>They’re resourceful tabloid journalists, and they reminisce about other times they went to great lengths to get their stories. They even hide a source within their office <em>furniture</em>. <strong>10/10 </strong></p>
<p id="uBoRVg"><strong>Are they ethical?</strong> That one’s dicier. They seem to have a very casual relationship with breaking the law—Hildy offhandedly mentions stealing a stomach from the coroner’s office—and Walter gets his ex-wife’s future mother-in-law arrested to get her out of the way of getting the story. <strong>4/10 </strong></p>
<p id="C2FsHn"><strong>How believable is the journalist? </strong>The banter is obviously way too snappy to be real, but the way <em>His Girl Friday </em>nails the excitement of actually making news captures the most romantic part of the job. <strong>7/10 </strong></p>
<p id="EIlq6B"><strong>Total: 31/40 </strong></p>
<h4 id="UmeCe7">8. Denzel Washington as Gray Grantham in<em> The Pelican Brief </em>
</h4>
  <figure class="e-image">
  <span class="e-image__inner">
    
    <span class="e-image__image " data-original="https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_asset/file/19394348/denzel_pelican_brief.jpg">
      
