<img srcset="https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/mRrsNSgXZGw8kXovOBxBBQIzHTc=/0x0:2480x1652/320x0/filters:focal(0x0:2480x1652):no_upscale()/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_asset/file/19394348/denzel_pelican_brief.jpg 320w, https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/Z-Upjvx68pTgggsaSA0vKMn59E8=/0x0:2480x1652/520x0/filters:focal(0x0:2480x1652):no_upscale()/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_asset/file/19394348/denzel_pelican_brief.jpg 520w, https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/O_NrddApzo5oSVudeXjswThZ8Fw=/0x0:2480x1652/720x0/filters:focal(0x0:2480x1652):no_upscale()/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_asset/file/19394348/denzel_pelican_brief.jpg 720w, https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/XIm-L9l_m5VPZ3AZKtF4g_xVejc=/0x0:2480x1652/920x0/filters:focal(0x0:2480x1652):no_upscale()/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_asset/file/19394348/denzel_pelican_brief.jpg 920w, https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/D7pHy9_tCKMahBOGzdGsIBe482w=/0x0:2480x1652/1120x0/filters:focal(0x0:2480x1652):no_upscale()/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_asset/file/19394348/denzel_pelican_brief.jpg 1120w, https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/Oqwqu8Ge5ViL6xFnMD1gCpdhhRA=/0x0:2480x1652/1320x0/filters:focal(0x0:2480x1652):no_upscale()/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_asset/file/19394348/denzel_pelican_brief.jpg 1320w, https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/KBejvKnp9T-C_jShglWRQJF6zSs=/0x0:2480x1652/1520x0/filters:focal(0x0:2480x1652):no_upscale()/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_asset/file/19394348/denzel_pelican_brief.jpg 1520w, https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/GTyJzK9C6lOroWL0Oe-kaDeJvnE=/0x0:2480x1652/1720x0/filters:focal(0x0:2480x1652):no_upscale()/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_asset/file/19394348/denzel_pelican_brief.jpg 1720w, https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/Dr7efQMzpPMs7GommjyEii5Lm_U=/0x0:2480x1652/1920x0/filters:focal(0x0:2480x1652):no_upscale()/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_asset/file/19394348/denzel_pelican_brief.jpg 1920w" sizes="(min-width: 1221px) 846px, (min-width: 880px) calc(100vw - 334px), 100vw" alt="" data-upload-width="2480" src="https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/s1ESk8iwOm0JSzaSWsojR4-RtpA=/0x0:2480x1652/1200x0/filters:focal(0x0:2480x1652):no_upscale()/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_asset/file/19394348/denzel_pelican_brief.jpg">

</source></picture>

      
    </span>
    
  </span>
  
    <span class="e-image__meta">
      
      
        <cite>Warner Bros.</cite>
      
    </span>
  
</figure>

<p id="xp6B9J">Grantham is a <em>Washington Herald</em> reporter who gets pulled on to a story about a plot to assassinate Supreme Court justices and soon becomes the target of assassination himself, along with Darby Shaw (Julia Roberts), a law student whose theory on the people behind the killings has put her in danger too. Grantham is also preposterously handsome. </p>
<p id="FrEFem"><strong>Does the character get their story? </strong>Yes! Even though people are trying to kill him and his source, Grantham publishes.<strong> 10/10 </strong></p>
<p id="iDB4fz"><strong>Are they competent? </strong>Yes. Shaw reaches out to Grantham because of his sterling reputation, and he is calm and clever while newsgathering. Shaw does do a lot of legwork for him, though, so I’ll knock off two points for his bounty of unpaid assistance. <strong>8/10 </strong></p>
<p id="ySPi1D"><strong>Are they ethical?</strong> Grantham is very by-the-book and also, notably, does NOT sleep with his hot and vulnerable source. <strong>10/10 </strong></p>
<p id="8ZXvI3"><strong>How believable is the journalist? </strong>Yes, however—a journalist that renowned and handsome would’ve been a celebrity of sorts in the ’90s, yet he seems to move through the world unrecognized.<strong> 6/10 </strong></p>
<p id="L579lJ"><strong>Total: 34/40 </strong></p>
<h4 id="wh6FtR">7. Courteney Cox as Gale Weathers in the <em>Scream</em> Franchise</h4>
<p id="nuiArX">Gale is a brash tabloid reporter who first appears in <em>Scream</em> after writing a book arguing that the wrong person was arrested for the murder of Sidney Prescott’s mother. (Turns out she’s right.) She then chases the story of the real killers throughout the series. </p>
<p id="E3T78U"><strong>Does the character get their story? </strong>Hell yes Gale Weathers gets her stories! She publishes multiple nonfiction books detailing the killing sprees that occur in the series, despite frequently being a target of the murderers. She is basically the mother of the True Crime drama, nearly 20 years before <em>Serial </em>launched. <strong>10/10 </strong></p>
<p id="WvtVWG"><strong>Are they competent? </strong>Yes, she’s dogged and skeptical and willing to stay on a story even when her coworkers are murdered.<strong> 10/10 </strong></p>
<p id="9tB1Iq"><strong>Are they ethical?</strong> This is Gale’s weak point; even though she gains more of a conscience throughout the series, she does some shady shit, like planting a video camera at a teen house party. <strong>3/10 </strong></p>
<p id="ftOVcy"><strong>How believable is the journalist? </strong>The unbelievability of the sheer number of serial killers she manages to encounter aside, Gale’s personality is imminently believable, and Cox plays her with delightfully slimy charm. <strong>10/10 </strong></p>
<p id="0bccoO"><strong>Bonus: </strong>plus-2 points for not dying<strong> </strong></p>
<p id="r1Ukng"><strong>Total: 35/40 </strong></p>
<h4 id="9xNqRm">6. Warren Beatty and Diane Keaton as John Reed and Louise Bryant in <em>Reds </em>(1981) </h4>
  <figure class="e-image">
  <span class="e-image__inner">
    
    <span class="e-image__image " data-original="https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_asset/file/19394350/diane_keaton_reds.jpg">
      
        <picture class="c-picture" data-cid="site/picture_element-1587430032_508_58893" data-cdata='{"asset_id":19394350,"ratio":"*"}'>
  


  <source srcset="https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/XmD8nfUzNtgAUVtxrp-7cHgdiu0=/0x0:1777x994/320x0/filters:focal(0x0:1777x994):format(webp):no_upscale()/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_asset/file/19394350/diane_keaton_reds.jpg 320w, https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/ITGn3FTh3y4pHMtjUKfXTZCJkqg=/0x0:1777x994/520x0/filters:focal(0x0:1777x994):format(webp):no_upscale()/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_asset/file/19394350/diane_keaton_reds.jpg 520w, https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/qsiZ0kbjvfYR-ZOaNfPDxvHd43s=/0x0:1777x994/720x0/filters:focal(0x0:1777x994):format(webp):no_upscale()/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_asset/file/19394350/diane_keaton_reds.jpg 720w, https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/UZ5UfE5cd96hZhr_bjg7NySMSVw=/0x0:1777x994/920x0/filters:focal(0x0:1777x994):format(webp):no_upscale()/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_asset/file/19394350/diane_keaton_reds.jpg 920w, https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/AB3gQZsMarX78OOX1grry21F-bE=/0x0:1777x994/1120x0/filters:focal(0x0:1777x994):format(webp):no_upscale()/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_asset/file/19394350/diane_keaton_reds.jpg 1120w, https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/Hq166WfOntb3oWD8OwkibWd7dBo=/0x0:1777x994/1320x0/filters:focal(0x0:1777x994):format(webp):no_upscale()/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_asset/file/19394350/diane_keaton_reds.jpg 1320w, https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/_XTNCja9f6XDqAvdCzRYq4KA0_E=/0x0:1777x994/1520x0/filters:focal(0x0:1777x994):format(webp):no_upscale()/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_asset/file/19394350/diane_keaton_reds.jpg 1520w, https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/yfzIh_YynYgZMjppVH3pRx56nPM=/0x0:1777x994/1720x0/filters:focal(0x0:1777x994):format(webp):no_upscale()/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_asset/file/19394350/diane_keaton_reds.jpg 1720w, https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/4YdpsHSx6x60LmoS_Wa3Bt3aCZ8=/0x0:1777x994/1920x0/filters:focal(0x0:1777x994):format(webp):no_upscale()/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_asset/file/19394350/diane_keaton_reds.jpg 1920w" sizes="(min-width: 1221px) 846px, (min-width: 880px) calc(100vw - 334px), 100vw" type="image/webp">


<img srcset="https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/kXbhGXv9AzDN1CCUSgEjQDjxVas=/0x0:1777x994/320x0/filters:focal(0x0:1777x994):no_upscale()/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_asset/file/19394350/diane_keaton_reds.jpg 320w, https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/--HDkoC2DliTQrhMJc7LmwAtM8s=/0x0:1777x994/520x0/filters:focal(0x0:1777x994):no_upscale()/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_asset/file/19394350/diane_keaton_reds.jpg 520w, https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/_fDR_ofDFygenmARNOTxeesCCuw=/0x0:1777x994/720x0/filters:focal(0x0:1777x994):no_upscale()/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_asset/file/19394350/diane_keaton_reds.jpg 720w, https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/6Jc6S8VkyAqYDNhTuGYLlxE24ag=/0x0:1777x994/920x0/filters:focal(0x0:1777x994):no_upscale()/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_asset/file/19394350/diane_keaton_reds.jpg 920w, https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/Qx_93flM7x6R6EnPIYZPLG5OFu0=/0x0:1777x994/1120x0/filters:focal(0x0:1777x994):no_upscale()/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_asset/file/19394350/diane_keaton_reds.jpg 1120w, https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/xzuob6r8itog-EJm8QyY6JR8DMM=/0x0:1777x994/1320x0/filters:focal(0x0:1777x994):no_upscale()/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_asset/file/19394350/diane_keaton_reds.jpg 1320w, https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/_Dzx-AiwsdSMPRwLT1zN7XbjKcM=/0x0:1777x994/1520x0/filters:focal(0x0:1777x994):no_upscale()/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_asset/file/19394350/diane_keaton_reds.jpg 1520w, https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/c_dcA5o2SQ5KUlnImm0_rSHuWJg=/0x0:1777x994/1720x0/filters:focal(0x0:1777x994):no_upscale()/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_asset/file/19394350/diane_keaton_reds.jpg 1720w, https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/RO8tdClnUxuX5sMJsLxKmLwRmC8=/0x0:1777x994/1920x0/filters:focal(0x0:1777x994):no_upscale()/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_asset/file/19394350/diane_keaton_reds.jpg 1920w" sizes="(min-width: 1221px) 846px, (min-width: 880px) calc(100vw - 334px), 100vw" alt="" data-upload-width="1777" src="https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/F1pQzDEnboPlVimATccnWRBdFKE=/0x0:1777x994/1200x0/filters:focal(0x0:1777x994):no_upscale()/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_asset/file/19394350/diane_keaton_reds.jpg">

</source></picture>

      
    </span>
    
  </span>
  
    <span class="e-image__meta">
      
      
        <cite>Paramount Pictures</cite>
      
    </span>
  
</figure>

<p id="yHr8EG">Beatty and Keaton play real-life married journalists and left-wing activists in an impossibly long movie that is somehow great despite devoting about an hour of its running time to big union infighting between the IWW and AFL. </p>
<p id="tMsIyn"><strong>Does the character get their story? </strong>Bryant ditches a dentist husband to become a successful reporter, while Reed writes <em>Ten Days That Shook the World</em>, still one of the best books ever about the Bolshevik Revolution.<strong> 10/10 </strong></p>
<p id="0sy76m"><strong>Are they competent? </strong>By the end of the film, Bryant has established herself as an independent journalist after struggling to gain recognition in her partner’s shadow. Reed is shown to be a great journalist, but he abandons reporting in favor of activism, so: <strong>6/10</strong></p>
<p id="165qzp"><strong>Are they ethical?</strong> Reed and Bryant are both obsessed with writing their way to a more just society and advocating for workers. That’s very good. <strong>10/10</strong></p>
<p id="lDDRJv"><strong>How believable is the journalist? </strong>It’s surprising that Keaton hasn’t played a journalist more frequently, because she has the right nervous energy and intensity. Beatty, meanwhile, seems like he’d be too handsome for it to work, but he gives Reed a flighty charm that keeps the movie from morphing into a hagiography. It works. <strong>10/10</strong></p>
<p id="s9fM0c"><strong>Total: 36/40 </strong></p>
<h4 id="9S2cQa">5. Rosamund Pike as Marie Colvin in <em>A Private War </em>(2018) </h4>
<p id="rFCttY">Pike plays real-life war correspondent Colvin in this underrated biopic. </p>
<p id="wzK66H"><strong>Does the character get their story? </strong>Yes, she gets hundreds of them, living fearlessly as a longtime war correspondent. <strong>10/10</strong> </p>
<p id="ggbaDV"><strong>Are they competent? </strong>Extremely, although she is shown to disregard her own personal safety. <strong>8/10 </strong></p>
<p id="ayUJvM"><strong>Are they ethical?</strong> Yes, she is a rigorous and scrupulous journalist. <strong>10/10 </strong></p>
<p id="qHNzwZ"><strong>How believable is the journalist? </strong>Pike does terrific character work, transforming herself into Colvin’s angular, haunted, tough cookie. <strong>10/10</strong> </p>
<p id="zFS4DA"><strong>Total: 38/40 </strong></p>
<h4 id="oAgNNR">4. Mark Ruffalo as Michael Rezendes, Rachel McAdams as Sacha Pfeiffer, etc., in <em>Spotlight </em>(2015)</h4>
  <figure class="e-image">
  <span class="e-image__inner">
    
    <span class="e-image__image " data-original="https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_asset/file/19394352/spotlight.jpg">
      
